{
  "texts": [
    "Among the diagnoses, 80.6% (n = 619), were classified as fulfilling the definition of a diagnosis, 75.9% (n=583) were deemed plausible, and 40.8% (n=313) were determined to be specific or highly specific.",
    "Of all the outputs generated, only 14.5% (n=27) had no diagnostic omissions and 14.0% (n=26) had omissions of diagnoses that were directly related to the input progress note.",
    "In addition, 32.5% (n=60) exhibited omissions from epistemic uncertainty.In the reasoning score components, for every sentence scored, 94.3% (n=781) were deemed to have little to no evidence of incorrect reading comprehension.",
    "Furthermore, 92.7% (n=767) had little to no evidence of incorrect recall of knowledge and 74% (n=613) exhibited little to no evidence of incorrect reasoning steps.",
    "Across the reasoning paragraphs generated for the 186 progress notes, 13.1% (n=108) did not contain an explanation for the generated diagnoses."
  ]
}